properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 3 at 1:41PM MST until January 4 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High winds returning to portions of central Wyoming
Saturday...

.An approaching cold front will bring strong winds to portions of
western and central Wyoming late tonight and Saturday.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range and Natrona
County Lower Elevations.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 8 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines.
Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Watch for strong cross winds on area roads.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM TO 8 PM MST SATURDAY
